        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1884-02-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1884-02-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="92" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d92">
                <head>No. 92.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Morton</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Frelinghuysen</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1884-02-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 6, 1884.</date>
                            (Received February 25.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 495.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your telegram received the 2d
                        ultimo, informing me that the Commercial Cable Company had obtained
                        permission to land on the coast of the United States, and requesting me to
                        ask that the same privilege be given to the company in France, I have the
                        honor to state that this application has been made and granted.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>LEVI P. MORTON.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
